Data are based on a sample and are subject to sampling variability. A margin of error is a measure of an estimates variability. The larger the margin of error in relation to the size of the estimates, the less reliable the estimate. When added to and subtracted from the estimate, the margin of error forms the 90 percent confidence interval.
